arguments.prompt:
You are implementing features for a Blazor Web App (Interactive Auto, Global mode with Individual auth) for a logistics company shipment tracker. The project is at `/tmp/sv-63cda4a767af44aeb1f58db16384beaa/ShipmentTracker/`.

**Project Structure:**
- `ShipmentTracker/` — Server project (hosts app, APIs, EF Core, Identity)
- `ShipmentTracker.Client/` — Client project (all interactive UI components)

**Key Architecture Rules (Auto Global mode):**
- All interactive components MUST go in the `.Client` project
- Components cannot access DbContext directly — use HTTP APIs
- Define service interfaces in `.Client`, implement with HttpClient there, implement with direct DB access in server
- Register matching services in both Program.cs files
- Don't add @rendermode to pages (global mode already configured)
- Identity/Account pages are static SSR — don't touch them

**Requirements:**
1. Dispatchers view a list of shipments with status and destination
2. Customers check their shipment status and estimated delivery
3. Role-based access: "Dispatcher" role sees all shipments; "Customer" role sees only their own
4. Every page has interactive controls (filters, search, refresh)

**Implementation Tasks:**

### 1. Data Model — Server project `Data/`

Create `ShipmentTracker/Data/Shipment.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Data;

public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public string? CustomerId { get; set; }
    public string CustomerName { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string? Notes { get; set; }
}

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Exception
}
```

### 2. Update ApplicationDbContext — add DbSet<Shipment>

Edit `ShipmentTracker/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs` to add:
```csharp
public DbSet<Shipment> Shipments => Set<Shipment>();
```

### 3. Shared DTO — Create in `.Client` project

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/ShipmentDto.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public class ShipmentDto
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Status { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public string CustomerName { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string? Notes { get; set; }
}
```

### 4. Service Interface — in `.Client` project

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/IShipmentService.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public interface IShipmentService
{
    Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetAllShipmentsAsync(string? statusFilter = null, string? search = null);
    Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetMyShipmentsAsync();
    Task<ShipmentDto?> GetByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber);
    Task UpdateStatusAsync(int id, string newStatus);
}
```
(Make sure to add `using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;`)

### 5. Client-side implementation using HttpClient

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentHttpService.cs`:
```csharp
using System.Net.Http.Json;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public class ShipmentHttpService : IShipmentService
{
    private readonly HttpClient _http;

    public ShipmentHttpService(HttpClient http)
    {
        _http = http;
    }

    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetAllShipmentsAsync(string? statusFilter = null, string? search = null)
    {
        var url = "/api/shipments";
        var query = new List<string>();
        if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(statusFilter)) query.Add($"status={Uri.EscapeDataString(statusFilter)}");
        if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(search)) query.Add($"search={Uri.EscapeDataString(search)}");
        if (query.Count > 0) url += "?" + string.Join("&", query);
        return await _http.GetFromJsonAsync<List<ShipmentDto>>(url) ?? [];
    }

    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetMyShipmentsAsync()
    {
        return await _http.GetFromJsonAsync<List<ShipmentDto>>("/api/shipments/mine") ?? [];
    }

    public async Task<ShipmentDto?> GetByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        return await _http.GetFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto?>($"/api/shipments/track/{Uri.EscapeDataString(trackingNumber)}");
    }

    public async Task UpdateStatusAsync(int id, string newStatus)
    {
        await _http.PutAsJsonAsync($"/api/shipments/{id}/status", new { Status = newStatus });
    }
}
```

### 6. Server-side implementation using EF Core

Create `ShipmentTracker/Services/ShipmentServerService.cs`:
```csharp
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Data;
using System.Security.Claims;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Http;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Services;

public class ShipmentServerService : IShipmentService
{
    private readonly ApplicationDbContext _db;
    private readonly IHttpContextAccessor _httpContextAccessor;

    public ShipmentServerService(ApplicationDbContext db, IHttpContextAccessor httpContextAccessor)
    {
        _db = db;
        _httpContextAccessor = httpContextAccessor;
    }

    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetAllShipmentsAsync(string? statusFilter = null, string? search = null)
    {
        var query = _db.Shipments.AsQueryable();
        if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(statusFilter) && Enum.TryParse<ShipmentStatus>(statusFilter, out var status))
            query = query.Where(s => s.Status == status);
        if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(search))
            query = query.Where(s => s.TrackingNumber.Contains(search) || s.Destination.Contains(search) || s.CustomerName.Contains(search));
        return await query.OrderByDescending(s => s.CreatedAt).Select(s => ToDto(s)).ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetMyShipmentsAsync()
    {
        var userId = _httpContextAccessor.HttpContext?.User.FindFirstValue(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier);
        if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(userId)) return [];
        return await _db.Shipments
            .Where(s => s.CustomerId == userId)
            .OrderByDescending(s => s.CreatedAt)
            .Select(s => ToDto(s))
            .ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<ShipmentDto?> GetByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        var s = await _db.Shipments.FirstOrDefaultAsync(s => s.TrackingNumber == trackingNumber);
        return s == null ? null : ToDto(s);
    }

    public async Task UpdateStatusAsync(int id, string newStatus)
    {
        if (!Enum.TryParse<ShipmentStatus>(newStatus, out var status)) return;
        var shipment = await _db.Shipments.FindAsync(id);
        if (shipment != null)
        {
            shipment.Status = status;
            await _db.SaveChangesAsync();
        }
    }

    private static ShipmentDto ToDto(Shipment s) => new()
    {
        Id = s.Id,
        TrackingNumber = s.TrackingNumber,
        Origin = s.Origin,
        Destination = s.Destination,
        Status = s.Status.ToString(),
        CreatedAt = s.CreatedAt,
        EstimatedDelivery = s.EstimatedDelivery,
        CustomerName = s.CustomerName,
        Notes = s.Notes
    };
}
```

### 7. API Endpoints — in server `Program.cs`

Add these API endpoints in the server `Program.cs` BEFORE `app.Run();` and AFTER `app.MapAdditionalIdentityEndpoints();`:

```csharp
// Shipment API endpoints
var shipmentApi = app.MapGroup("/api/shipments").RequireAuthorization();

shipmentApi.MapGet("/", async (string? status, string? search, IShipmentService service) =>
    Results.Ok(await service.GetAllShipmentsAsync(status, search)));

shipmentApi.MapGet("/mine", async (IShipmentService service) =>
    Results.Ok(await service.GetMyShipmentsAsync()));

shipmentApi.MapGet("/track/{trackingNumber}", async (string trackingNumber, IShipmentService service) =>
    await service.GetByTrackingNumberAsync(trackingNumber) is { } dto ? Results.Ok(dto) : Results.NotFound());

shipmentApi.MapPut("/{id}/status", async (int id, StatusUpdateRequest request, IShipmentService service) =>
{
    await service.UpdateStatusAsync(id, request.Status);
    return Results.NoContent();
});
```

Also add this record at the bottom of Program.cs (or in a separate file):
```csharp
public record StatusUpdateRequest(string Status);
```

Add `using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;` at the top of Program.cs.

Also register the services in server Program.cs (before `var app = builder.Build();`):
```csharp
builder.Services.AddHttpContextAccessor();
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentServerService>();
```
Add `using ShipmentTracker.Services;` too.

### 8. Register services in Client Program.cs

Update `ShipmentTracker.Client/Program.cs`:
```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.Hosting;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

var builder = WebAssemblyHostBuilder.CreateDefault(args);

builder.Services.AddAuthorizationCore();
builder.Services.AddCascadingAuthenticationState();
builder.Services.AddAuthenticationStateDeserialization();

builder.Services.AddScoped(sp => new HttpClient { BaseAddress = new Uri(builder.HostEnvironment.BaseAddress) });
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentHttpService>();

await builder.Build().RunAsync();
```

### 9. Pages in `.Client` project

**Remove** the default Counter.razor page from `ShipmentTracker.Client/Pages/`.

**Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Pages/Shipments.razor`** — Dispatcher view:
```razor
@page "/shipments"
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization
@using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models
@using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services
@attribute [Authorize(Roles = "Dispatcher")]
@inject IShipmentService ShipmentService

<PageTitle>All Shipments</PageTitle>

<h1>Shipments</h1>

<div class="row mb-3">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Search tracking #, destination, customer..."
               @bind="searchTerm" @bind:event="oninput" @onkeyup="HandleSearch" />
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <select class="form-select" @bind="statusFilter" @bind:after="LoadShipments">
            <option value="">All Statuses</option>
            <option value="Pending">Pending</option>
            <option value="PickedUp">Picked Up</option>
            <option value="InTransit">In Transit</option>
            <option value="OutForDelivery">Out for Delivery</option>
            <option value="Delivered">Delivered</option>
            <option value="Exception">Exception</option>
        </select>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-2">
        <button class="btn btn-primary" @onclick="LoadShipments">
            <span class="bi bi-arrow-clockwise"></span> Refresh
        </button>
    </div>
</div>

@if (loading)
{
    <p><em>Loading shipments...</em></p>
}
else if (shipments.Count == 0)
{
    <p>No shipments found.</p>
}
else
{
    <table class="table table-striped table-hover">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Tracking #</th>
                <th>Customer</th>
                <th>Origin</th>
                <th>Destination</th>
                <th>Status</th>
                <th>Est. Delivery</th>
                <th>Actions</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            @foreach (var s in shipments)
            {
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>@s.TrackingNumber</strong></td>
                    <td>@s.CustomerName</td>
                    <td>@s.Origin</td>
                    <td>@s.Destination</td>
                    <td><span class="badge @GetStatusBadge(s.Status)">@FormatStatus(s.Status)</span></td>
                    <td>@(s.EstimatedDelivery?.ToString("MMM dd, yyyy") ?? "—")</td>
                    <td>
                        <select class="form-select form-select-sm" style="width:auto;display:inline-block"
                                value="@s.Status" @onchange="e => UpdateStatus(s, e)">
                            <option value="Pending">Pending</option>
                            <option value="PickedUp">Picked Up</option>
                            <option value="InTransit">In Transit</option>
                            <option value="OutForDelivery">Out for Delivery</option>
                            <option value="Delivered">Delivered</option>
                            <option value="Exception">Exception</option>
                        </select>
                    </td>
                </tr>
            }
        </tbody>
    </table>
}

@code {
    private List<ShipmentDto> shipments = [];
    private string searchTerm = "";
